name: Heather Offer
bio: Wife. Twin Mom. Books. Health-ish. Assistant to @thesisterstudioig 💕 Travel and make memories!!

social_posts.post_text: Happy December!! 📷 @photographybyelizabethann

365 days without you, we miss you so very much!! This week has been extremely hard on us, well no day is easy but this week has been extra hard.  It sometimes still doesn’t seem real, but I feel so thankful knowing you are watching over us daily. #wemissyoudad
The twins didn’t want to see Santa this year and it honestly made me so sad, made me realize how fast they are growing up. 😭 Time slow down.
Merry Christmas Eve from me and this silly family!!! 📷 @photographybyelizabethann

2022 was one of the best years for us!! We celebrated so many birthdays which included quite a few trips which included Mexico, Nola, and Miami, we watched my best friend of over 20 years marry her best friend, we went to Mexico to celebrate another, and we ended the year with so many laughs, tears and cheers!! I am excited for 2023 and the year it’s going to be for all of us!!!
Let’s do this 2023!!!
Some snaps from our 2022 trips. I can’t wait to see where 2023 takes us. #takethetrips

What started out as a such slow read, ended up being one of my favorite books by Nicholas Sparks. I actually got this book a while ago and couldn’t get into it so I put it away for a bit, eventually bringing it back out during the holiday break and let me say, I am so glad I did. Part 2 is when everything changed for me and I become hooked. In my opinion, it wasn’t the typical Nicholas Sparks book, it definitely had some turns I didn’t see coming and wow the ending took me by surprise. Now what’s next? Do I go romantic or thriller?? 🤔

I debated sharing this book, not because it’s bad, because it’s far from bad. It’s soooo good but it’s VERY spicy and very inappropriate. Basically, if you like 50 shades, you will like this is all I can say. It’s 500 pages and it had me hooked in the first 10 and I read it in 3 days. Yes, 3 days. It’s that good!!! Oh and it is a series so you better believe, I already ordered the second book. Jen will also tell you I talked her head off about it. 😜 So grab yourself your favorite beverage and get to reading!! #offerreads
Had the best time in Fredericksburg drinking all the wine and celebrating @shannontram birthday!!! 🍷 ❤️ 💃

A long weekend in Santa Fe was exactly what we all needed!!! My kids loved snowboarding and Averie was able to go down a green without any help. 👏 Both kids didn’t want to leave and already asking about going back. Already talking about where we will go next year. 😜
This years auction theme was Saturday Night Live and it didn’t disappoint. Such a fun night with the school families.

This book gave me so many emotions. First, it started out soooo slow that I kept debating if I should finish it. Once I got into it, I loved it. It’s very different and gave me quite a few emotions. ❤️❤️❤️ #offerreads

Happy 40th to you, @heather.rude.gooden . I’m so thankful that you came into my life 25 years ago. We have been through it all. From drill team line, spending most of our high school days at your house, to college and our first apartments, to working together on the island, multiple vacations, my wedding, you being there when twins were born, your wedding, the list could go on…..we have so many memories together and I can’t wait to see what the next 40 years bring you my friend, my twin, my soul sister. I love you and hope you feel all the love today, Heather!!
Today was a busy day!! Averie was teacher of the day, Bentley won Hall of Famer for his class and then this evening we had the talent show that these girls have been working so hard to do. 👏

Happy 12 years Andrew! We have been through the things and yet we continue to be stronger and better. You’re so lucky to have me but I am blessed to have you! Thanks for being my rock and being there through it all and loving me unconditionally. You’re the real deal!!!

Happy 10th Birthday to my babies! I can’t believe y’all are 10. I hope this year all your dreams come true! Bentley is the sweetest boy with the biggest heart who recently fell in love with Lacrosse. Averie is me in so many ways but she is braver and smarter than I could ever think of. Now stop growing up and be my babies forever!!!
Had the best few days in the sunshine celebrating Jared turning 50!!

Our Spring break 2023 consisted of the lazy River and water slides, visiting the Alamo, seeing some cool caves, playing on the river walk, lots of yummy food and hours of playing games. I would say it was a win win!!!

Our schools first Color Run was a success! Me and this girl right here worked our tails off the past couple of months and weeks leading up to the event. We laughed a lot, cried a little 😜, made so many memories together and it was all worth it to see all the kids and even parents have a blast!! What’s next @poohblair99
Annual girl trips are good for the soul!!!!
Taylor Swift!! Last night was seriously one of the best nights of my life!! I can’t stop smiling today. 🫶

A close friend highly recommended this book and I am so glad she did. It was a quick and easy read. From someone who has always wanted to visit Italy, this made me realize I MUST visit there one day. The entire story just touched me, such a cute read.
Happy Easter!!!

A quick weekend trip with my mom to Hot Springs was what we both needed. We shopped, we drank yummy drinks, we gambled, we laughed a lot and my mom shared lots of memories of my step dad. Such a fun and memorable weekend.
Had such a fun weekend in Austin celebrating the gorgeous Grace!!! #bacheloretteparty #thecouncil4life

I felt like this needed it’s own spot on my feed!! Mainly bc I forgot to put it in my reel and too lazy to make a new one 😜 but also because these girls made me laugh soooo much this past weekend!! Anna and her cousin are seriously soooo fun!! They stuck with me for life now. 😘

A quick 24 hour trip to CA to Fiesta Friday to celebrate the launch of @drinkhorton by @krista.horton was one of the coolest nights ever. 🎉 🪅 Also thank you @thesisterstudioig for letting me tag along. Soooo fun!!!!
So glad I was able to make it home Saturday just in time to celebrate Jessica Birthday!! Couldn’t miss celebrating your last year in your 30s @jesbaldwin
Mission 4 complete!! Space party was sooooo fun!!!
Mother’s Day Brunch with my momma!! I love you, mom!!
The best type of Sunday Funday hanging with so many fun people celebrating @kingdomofsequins Seltzer Olympics! I can’t wait for next year. Cheers!!

Just finished this book and let me tell you the ending definitely peaked my interest. The first book in this series I read in 24 hours but this one has taken me a long time, and it wasn’t until the middle that I finally got into it. But if being honest, I wasn’t loving what was happening so debated if I would even read book 3, but now based off the ending, I must go on. So next up is book 3….. 

#offerreads #books
Memorial Day weekend with friends was seriously one of the best weekends we have had. Love making memories with these families.
Made it home just in time to spend Memorial Day with the neighbors.
Ice cream for breakfast is okay during the summer, right?? 😜 😂

Wow, talk about a week! This was one of those weeks that I will be talking about for weeks to come. I got to be part of a extremely cool experience watching my boss aka best friend be on national TV. Like what???!?? Then we got to introduce the guys to one of our favorite cities, the weather was absolutely perfect, we ate some yummy food, we did all the touristy things and made soooo many memories. 🤟NYC!!!

The kid hat of the summer! Just got Bentley & Averie their official @theswaptop hats and they were so excited!! Each hat comes with 7 jibbitz that are interchangeable with crocs. Winning. 🙌 They seriously make the best gift for kiddos!! Go check them out @theswaptop
Happy Birthday, Mama!! We love you sooooo much and so thankful for each day we have with you.
Happy 45th Birthday, Kelle!! Loved celebrating you sweet friend!! @kelledawn
July 4th!! 💥
Today was absolutely fabulous!!!! Loved celebrating you and Baby Emerson today @just.meesh

This book is soooooo good! Like so good! It gave me all the emotions someone can feel. If you enjoy a good love story, then I highly recommend this one. Make sure to read to the epilogue. 😭 ♥️♥️ #offerreads  Thank you for the recommendation @fleurdille
Broken Bow 2023!! I love this time with our families and love watching these kiddos grow up together!! Feeling very grateful!!!

This book was sooooo good! I listened to it on audible when I was doing things around the house, while in the car, and on my walks. I wanted to have it playing anytime I could. I loved how it kept me on my toes. All you can do is root for Wyn and Harriet with all your heart. I’m a hopeless romantic and this book hit all my heart strings!! 🥰#offerreads

This book was seriously one that left my mouth open. I read it in a couple days and I am still in shock of all the twists and turns. It’s one of those ones you think you figured out and nope….. #offerrreads
Bahamas, I love you!! One of the best trips we have ever had and it was the perfect way to end a pretty perfect summer. Memories that we will never forget.

Alll I can say is brave yourself with this one, still trying to understand what all just happened. 🤯 I seriously listened to this nonstop on audible in the last few days. I might need a PG movie now. 😳 okay, who am I kidding, going to start the 2nd one asap. 😜 #offerreads
Last year of elementary! 5th grade, let’s do this while I go in a corner cry that my babies are growing up way tooooo fast. 😭

Happy Birthday to the best of the best, Jen Reed! You are the greatest friend with the biggest heart. I cannot imagine my life without you. Thank you for being the real deal, putting up with me for over 15 years, going on multiple vacations, making me laugh daily, and being a shoulder to cry on, your always there and I hope today you feel loved and appreciated!! You deserve the world friend!!! @thesisterstudioig

Best job with the best team in the best city makes the best week!! Jen, thank you for every opportunity, every meeting, every conversation, every moment, you have done so much for me and my family. I love you and continue to be soooo proud of you!! What’s next?? 😘

Finished this on audible a couple days ago and still shaken up. It wasn’t as good as the first one but still kept me on my toes. I would definitely recommend reading the first one before starting this one… #offerreads

Finally finished this book! I love everything about this series! I smiled, laughed and cried. It touch my momma strings, my friend strings, and truly I felt all the emotions. I can’t wait for the final season to come out on TV. I have to ask…..Are you team Conrad or team Jeremiah?? #offerreads

Happy Birthday to my hubby, Andrew! We love you!! You make us laugh and smile every single day. We love how you got jokes for days, you will always dance with Averie in the living room, watching football games with Bentley on the couch, you’re always down for a good costume party, will have a margarita any time of the day, and you are loyal to the people you truly care about and will bend over backwards for those people. You love big and believe in second chances, and even though you seem a little tough on the outside, you are really just a teddy bear. We love you and hope you feel the love all year long!!! Happy 41st!!!
Family, live music, yummy food and drinks, good laughs and lots of memories were made in Nashville!!
Savannah + neighbors + drinks + yummy food + lots of laughs = a good time!!!!

Happy Thanksgiving from my family to yours!! So thankful for each of you and this space!!! 

📷 @photographybyelizabethann
Love this little family of mine…… thank you for capturing these overdue photos @photographybyelizabethann
December in New York….I vote, absolutely!! Such a magical and special week introducing the kids to one of the best cities!! Very extra thankful for this trip!!
Merry Christmas!!!!!
December comes to an end…….

2023 was such an amazing year filled with so many laughs, incredible vacations, memories that will last a lifetime and so much more. I welcome a new year ahead and can’t wait to see what it brings for each of you. Cheers!!!!
Another recap of 2023, because why not…… 😘 😜

I finished this book back in November but due to holidays, just now sharing.😜 This book was so cute and such a fun and easy read. If you’re about to go on a vacation, I would recommend it. Or looking for something quick and easy, this is the book for you. I don’t think you will be disappointed. 🙌#offerreads

This book was soooo cute! It started out really slow, I actually had borrowed from my girlfriend a few months ago and then couldn’t get into it so put it away for a while. She told me to give it a second chance and I am so glad I did. It was pretty predictable but the story was cute and for someone who loves LOVE, this hit alll my heart strings! #offerreads
Averie & Bentley got to experience their first Stars Game last night and it was a BIG hit!! I love watching hockey and love that they found a new love as well. Go Stars!!!
